<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=28 g=1 f=1 -->
, 27 FCC 2d 723 (1971), an FM application was judged on the basis of ``degree of completeness'' and rejected because
it omitted the entire engineering and EEO sections and significant portions of the legal, financial and ascertainment
sections. The Commission concluded that it lacked ``sufficient information to reach many of the necessary determinations
regarding the adequacy of the proposal *&blank;*&blank;*'' 
